That's weird and it shouldn't happen. Can you show a screenshot of the workflow and also the custom code? The simplest thing to do is to just do a trace to debug it. I'd start with the following and see what you get:
```exports.main = async (event, callback) =&gt; {
  console.log(event.inputFields['contact_id']);
  console.log(event.inputFields['customer_number']);
  console.log(event.inputFields['vat']);
 return;
}```
Try it without a delay, just a basic workflow with your triggers (don't forget your re-enrollment triggers) and see if the data is outputted in your Action logs.
